definition: appearance/portrait/picture/government minister/(physics) phase/(literary) to appraise (esp. by scrutinizing physical features)/to read sb's fortune (by physiognomy, palmistry etc)
each other/one another/mutually/fret on the neck of a pipa 琵琶[pi2 pa5] (a fret on the soundboard is called a 品[pin3])

sentences.english: I do not know you so I can not say if I have love for you in my heart.
sentences.chinese: 我們仍然素不相識，因此我還不能肯定是否真心愛你。

sentences.english: I got to ask total strangers the things I'd always wanted to know.
sentences.chinese: 我向素不相識的人們打探我一直想知道的事。

sentences.english: The Sichuan earthquake gave witness to the kindness of strangers in an emergency.
sentences.chinese: 四川大地震見證了危難中的那些素不相識者的善舉。
